    • askAddModule

      public void askAddModule()
      Conducts all the checks and considerations before actually adding the module. Prompts user to input the desired course code ,and subsequently list out the currently available indices and their respective vacancies. Then, this method retrieves the chosen Index object from the database, and considers the various exceptions and scenarios like overlapping of timetable schedule, adding of existing index etc. If index has no vacancy, student is added into the waitlist. Otherwise, student is able to successfully add module.

    • doAddModule

      public void doAddModule​(Index indexToAdd)
      Executes the adding of module. Adds the new module to the student's module list, and at the same time, adds student into the respective Index's student list.
      Parameters:
      indexToAdd - Desired index to be added

    • askDropModule

      public java.lang.String[] askDropModule​(boolean drop) throws java.lang.Exception
      Conducts all the checks and considerations before dropping the module. Prints all existing courses that student is taking, prompts user to input choice. For the dropping of module, the implementation method doDropModule() is called. Otherwise, the desired module is not dropped but returned. Note: This method fulfills 2 actions: (1) Drop module and a part of (2) Swap module
      Parameters:
      drop - true to drop module, false to swap module
      Returns:
      mod Array of Strings that contain the module's courseCode and index
      Throws:
      e - Prompts user for valid integer input when choosing desired index
      java.lang.Exception

    • doDropModule

      public java.lang.String[] doDropModule​(int removeChoice) throws java.lang.Exception
      Executes the dropping of module. Removes the dropped module from the student's module list, and at the same time, removes student from the respective Index's student list. If there is a non-empty waitlist for that index, the first element will be popped and added into the index.
      Parameters:
      removeChoice - Integer that represents the array index of the student's module list of the module to be dropped
      Throws:
      java.lang.Exception

    • swapIndex

      public void swapIndex()
      Executes the swapping of index with another student. Prompts user to choose which module to be dropped, and the username of the other student. Performs swapping of students in the respective indices student lists.

    • changeIndex

      public void changeIndex()
      Executes the changing of index with another index of the same module. Prints all existing courses that student is taking, prompts user to input choice. Performs error handling to ensure that it is a valid change, and updates the student lists of the relevant indices.

    • printModules

      public void printModules()
      Prints all the course codes and indices taken by the student in a table format.

    • promptToJoinWaitList

      public boolean promptToJoinWaitList​(Index indexToAdd)
      Checks if index vacancy is zero and prompts user to join waitlist if there is no vacancy in the desired index. If yes is chosen, append user to waitlist.
      Parameters:
      indexToAdd - index to be added
      Returns:
      true if vacancy of desired index is 0, otherwise false
